Physiphora clausa (
Macquart, 1843
)
(
Figs 10–19
)

Wing. Completely hyaline, postero­apical extension of cell cup long, about 2.0 times as long as transverse section of vein CuA 2 , cell r 4 + 5 completely closed, forming petiolate at wing tip (
Fig. 13
).

Abdomen. Both tergites and sternites brown or black­brown, with green, red­golden, purple or blue reflection; abdominal tergite 2 yellowish white setulose on sides. Male postabdomen (
Figs. 15–19
) yellow, otherwise as described for P. a l c e a e . Female terminalia: aculeus 6.5–8 times as long as wide at base, similar to that of
P. alceae
(
Fig. 14
); 3 spherical spermathecae (
Fig. 12
).
